Description: Ravenpaw’s life on the farm is threatened by some rogue cats seeking shelter.
Title: WARRIORS: RAVENPAW’S PATH, VOL. 3
Author: Erin Hunter and James Barry
Contributor: by Erin Hunter and James Barry

Description: Tsukune Aono’s new school is filled with vampires and werewolves. And the girl he is interested seems to have eyes for him, but is it his blood she’s after?
Title: ROSARIO + VAMPIRE: SEASON II, VOL. 2
Author: Akihisa Ikeda

Description: Misao Harada can see into a magical realm where she is the bride demon of prophecy. How will she survive the pursuit of demons who want the power in her blood?
Title: BLACK BIRD, VOL. 5
Author: Kanoko Sakurakoji

Description: This manga series features the further adventures of the characters from the 1986 film “Labyrinth,” directed by Jim Henson. Toby may have returned home at the end of the movie, but now the Goblin King wants him back.
Title: RETURN TO LABYRINTH, VOL. 4
Author: Jake T Forbes and Chris Lie
Contributor: by Jake T. Forbes and Chris Lie

Description: Can Negi win the tournament of champions against Jack Ravan, a martial arts legend?
Title: NEGIMA! MAGISTER NEGI MAGI, VOL. 27
Author: Ken Akamatsu

Description: This manga series is about Moritaka Mashiro, who enjoys drawing and Akito Takagi, a would-be writer, who team up to create a manga series. Will they survive the world of publishing?
Title: BAKUMAN, VOL. 1
Author: Tsugumi Ohba and Takeshi Obata
Contributor: by Tsugumi Ohba and Takeshi Obata

Description: The origins and true nature of Pain, Naruto’s arch nemesis, are revealed.
Title: NARUTO, VOL. 48
Author: Masashi Kishimoto

Description: The protagonist: 15-year-old Allen Walker. The setting: 19th century England. His mission: to find Innocence, a substance used to create weapons to destroy the akuma demons.
Title: D. GRAY-MAN, VOL. 18
Author: Katsura Hoshino

Description: Two brothers harmed in a ritual that was half magic/half science seek the legendary Philosopher’s Stone to make things right.
Title: FULLMETAL ALCHEMIST, VOL. 23
Author: Hiromu Arakawa

Description: A woman’s work is never done: Can Kyoko balance revenge, a career and her own happiness?
Title: SKIP BEAT!, VOL. 21
Author: Yoshiki Nakamura
